{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, a filtering operation can be viewed as an additional type of the 6th-order diffusion (see the Appendix in Popescu Braileanu, Lukin, and Khomenko, 2023),",
    "Figure 3 The second-order density perturbation as a function of height, in a 1D experiment of a monochromatic Alfvén wave propagation from the bottom photosphere upwards in a stratified solar atmosphere permeated by a constant magnetic field.",
    "Solid black line: no filtering is applied.",
    "Dashed red line: filtering is applied.",
    "where ν F 6 is the diffusion coefficient."
  ]
}